ðŸš€ RETRO FUTURISM STYLE GUIDE
================================================================================

VISUAL LANGUAGE:
- **Form**: 80s/90s inspired, warm analog-meets-digital aesthetic
- **Colors**: Warm sunset palette (#f97316, #fbbf24, #fb923c), coral/peach, vintage cyan, cream backgrounds
- **Typography**: Bold geometric sans (Archivo Black, Outfit) + retro monospace (Courier, Space Mono)
- **Shapes**: Medium rounded (0.75rem) or soft squares, gradient overlays, scan-line effects
- **Interaction**: Retro transitions (linear), VHS glitch effects (optional), warm glow on hover

DESIGN TOKENS GUIDANCE:
- Background: Warm cream (#fef3c7), soft peach, or dark with warm tint (#2d1b16)
- Primary: Orange/coral gradient (#f97316 â†’ #fbbf24), warm glow
- Surface: Gradient cards with subtle noise texture, warm shadows
- Radius: 0.75rem (balanced rounded)
- Shadow: Warm-tinted shadows (orange/red glow), medium spread
- Animation: 200-400ms linear or stepped easing (retro feel)

COMPONENT PATTERNS:
- Buttons: Gradient fills (orangeâ†’yellow), chunky with warm glow, slight bevel effect
- Cards: Gradient backgrounds, subtle grain/noise texture, warm border glow
- Inputs: Thick borders, warm focus state, inner bevel/emboss (subtle)
- Text: Bold for headings, use gradients sparingly, retro color palette

LAYOUT & SPACING:
- Structured grids with vintage proportions
- Moderate spacing (py-12, py-20)
- Hero sections with bold typography and sunset gradients
- Background: Gradient overlays (warm), grid patterns, retro shapes (circles, triangles)

ATMOSPHERE:
- Nostalgic yet forward-looking
- Optimistic, energetic, analog warmth
- 80s tech aesthetic meets modern UX
- Warmth through color temperature and glows

DO NOT:
- Use cold blue tones as primary
- Create overly smooth, modern gradients
- Skip texture or grain overlays
- Use thin, delicate typography

================================================================================

